h3cVoCallActive.name: h3cVoCallActive

revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB file.

h3cVoCallActive.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China Http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
h3cVoCallActive.description: This MIB file is to provide the definition of voice call active record information.

H3cGUid.name: H3cGUid
H3cGUid.description: Represents a global call identifier. The global call identifier is used as an unique identifier for an end-to-end call. A zero length H3cGUid indicates no value for the global call identifier.

h3cVoiceCallActiveTable.name: h3cVoiceCallActiveTable
h3cVoiceCallActiveTable.description: This table is the voice extension to the call active table of DIAL-CONTROL-MIB. It contains voice encapsulation call leg information that is derived from the statistics of lower layer telephony interface.

h3cVoiceCallActiveEntry.name: h3cVoiceCallActiveEntry
h3cVoiceCallActiveEntry.description: The information regarding a single voice encapsulation call leg. The call leg entry is identified by using the same index objects that are used by call active table of DIAL-CONTROL-MIB to identify the call. An entry of this table is created when its associated call active entry in the DIAL-CONTROL-MIB is created and call active entry contains the call establishment to a voice over telephony network peer. The entry is deleted when its associated call active entry in the DIAL-CONTROL-MIB is deleted.

h3cVoCallActiveConnectionId.name: h3cVoCallActiveConnectionId
h3cVoCallActiveConnectionId.description: The global call identifier for the gateway call.

h3cVoCallActiveTxDuration.name: h3cVoCallActiveTxDuration
h3cVoCallActiveTxDuration.description: Duration of transmit path open from this peer to the voice gateway for the call. The units is milliseconds.

h3cVoCallActiveVoiceTxDuration.name: h3cVoCallActiveVoiceTxDuration
h3cVoCallActiveVoiceTxDuration.description: Duration of voice transmitted from this peer to voice gateway for this call. The voice utilization rate can be obtained by dividing this by h3cVoCallActiveTXDuration object. The units is milliseconds.

h3cVoCallActiveFaxTxDuration.name: h3cVoCallActiveFaxTxDuration
h3cVoCallActiveFaxTxDuration.description: Duration of fax transmitted from this peer to voice gateway for this call. The fax utilization rate can be obtained by dividing this by h3cVoCallActiveTXDuration object. The units is milliseconds.

h3cVoCallActiveCoderType.name: h3cVoCallActiveCoderType
h3cVoCallActiveCoderType.description: The negotiated coder type. It specifies the encode type to the PSTN leg of a call.

h3cVoCallActiveImgPageCount.name: h3cVoCallActiveImgPageCount
h3cVoCallActiveImgPageCount.description: The number of fax related image pages are received or transmitted via the peer for the call. The units is pages.

h3cVoiceVoIPCallActiveTable.name: h3cVoiceVoIPCallActiveTable
h3cVoiceVoIPCallActiveTable.description: This table is the VoIP extension to the call active table of DIAL-CONTROL-MIB. It contains VoIP call leg information about specific VoIP call destination.

h3cVoiceVoIPCallActiveEntry.name: h3cVoiceVoIPCallActiveEntry
h3cVoiceVoIPCallActiveEntry.description: The information regarding a single VoIP call leg. The call leg entry is identified by using the same index objects that are used by call active table of DIAL-CONTROL-MIB to identify the call. An entry of this table is created when its associated call active entry in the DIAL-CONTROL-MIB is created and the call active entry contains information for the call establishment to the peer on the IP backbone via a voice over IP peer. The entry is deleted when its associated call active entry in the DIAL-CONTROL-MIB is deleted.

h3cVoVoIPCallActiveConnectionId.name: h3cVoVoIPCallActiveConnectionId
h3cVoVoIPCallActiveConnectionId.description: The global call identifier for the gateway call.

h3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemSigIPType.name: h3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemSigIPType
h3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemSigIPType.description: The type of remote system signalling IP address for the VoIP call.

h3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemSigIPAddr.name: h3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemSigIPAddr
h3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemSigIPAddr.description: Remote system signalling IP address for the VoIP call.

h3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemSigPort.name: h3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemSigPort
h3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemSigPort.description: Remote system UDP listener signalling port to which to transmit voice packets.

h3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemMedIPType.name: h3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemMedIPType
h3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemMedIPType.description: The type of remote system media IP address for the VoIP call.

h3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemMedIPAddr.name: h3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemMedIPAddr
h3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemMedIPAddr.description: Remote system media IP address for the VoIP call.

h3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemMedPort.name: h3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemMedPort
h3cVoVoIPCallActiveRemMedPort.description: Remote system UDP listener media port to which to transmit voice packets.

h3cVoVoIPCallActiveSessProtocol.name: h3cVoVoIPCallActiveSessProtocol
h3cVoVoIPCallActiveSessProtocol.description: The object specifies the session protocol to be used for internet call between local and remote router via IP backbone.

h3cVoVoIPCallActiveCoderType.name: h3cVoVoIPCallActiveCoderType
h3cVoVoIPCallActiveCoderType.description: The negotiated coder type. It specifies the encode type to the VoIP leg of a call.
